description: A narrow beach of dusky granite gravel provides a small gap between the river to the west and the encroaching forest, a dense thicket of young willows, and thorn-covered vines.  A brace of curlews wades through the edge of the river, digging through the mud of the shallows.
title: [Mistydeep, Eastern Shore]
location: the northern reaches of the Mistydeep River
